&lt;p&gt;Schrödinger seeks a &lt;strong&gt;Student Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; to join us in our mission to improve human health and quality of life through the development, distribution, and application of advanced computational methods.&amp;nbsp; This is a 20-hour-per-week position, for six to twelve months, with a monthly salary of 1,500 €.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will provide crucial administrative and operational support to the Schrödinger Europe team in &lt;strong&gt;Mannheim&lt;/strong&gt;. This is a fantastic opportunity to gain hands-on experience in office management, HR operations, and event coordination within a dynamic corporate environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work under the direct guidance and supervision of experienced team members who will support your growth and help you succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please submit in English and include a cover letter with your application that indicates your availability for work Monday - Friday.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who will love this job:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive and detail-oriented university student with strong organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent communicator (written and verbal) with the ability to interact professionally with visitors and team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team player with a positive attitude and a willingness to learn under supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in overseeing the Mannheim office, including greeting visitors and creating a welcoming environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help order office supplies and coordinate routine office maintenance work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the coordination of business trips, travel management, and the organization of internal office events and meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the team in organizing and executing successful customer events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain the inventory of marketing materials and coordinate shipments to various conferences and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review credit card receipts and assist in preparing accuracy reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team with weekly payment runs and related administrative documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the hiring pipeline by scheduling job interviews and coordinating communication with candidates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active enrollment in a university degree program (Business Administration, HR, Communication, or a related field is a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) or Google Workspace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English and German&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay and perks:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours tailored to complement your university schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive, supervised environment designed to help you develop professional skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insights into global team operations, HR, and finance workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you’re in the office you can profit from our central location, the charging of personal devices with green energy, stocked kitchens with coffee/tea, fruit, snacks, and beverages, and the organization of team-building and social events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sound exciting? Apply today and join us!&lt;/p&gt;
