&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Schrödinger seeks a &lt;strong&gt;Vice President of Marketing&lt;/strong&gt; to join us in our mission to improve human health and quality of life through the development, distribution, and application of advanced computational methods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a leader on our Marketing team, reporting to the Chief Commercial Officer (CCO), you’ll architect our global marketing strategy and be responsible for building a full-funnel engagement engine that converts scientific interest into measurable commercial growth. In this role, you will elevate Schrödinger’s corporate brand equity and category leadership, while scaling a predictable lead-to-revenue machine that supports our mission to revolutionize drug discovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who will love this job:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growth architect with a proven track record of scaling B2B SaaS or Life Science marketing organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A science aficionado who can translate complex workflows into compelling business outcomes in collaboration with chemists and other computational researchers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A data strategist and AI innovator who leverages attribution insights, GTM optimization, and real-time intent signals to build a predictable revenue engine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent team player who thrives in cross-functional environments (this hire will connect Product R&amp;amp;D, Global Portfolio Leaders, and Sales teams)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the CCO and Global Portfolio Leaders to define go-to-market strategies for our Life Sciences and our Materials Science suites, ensuring product positioning translates directly into the commercial pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the global lead generation quota; develop and execute data-driven marketing strategies to aggressively grow marketing-qualified and sales-accepted leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map and optimize the buyers’ journey, from winning attention through developing initial awareness and affecting advocacy, utilizing HubSpot, HighSpot, Salesforce and other technologies to track attribution and ROI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct the creation of high-impact technical content (white papers, case studies, webinars) designed to capture interest, build intent, and move pharma/biotech decision-makers through to the Sales funnel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify emerging trends and competitive shifts in the market, ensuring Schrödinger’s value propositions remain the gold standard in computational chemistry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least ten years of marketing leadership experience (at least five years in B2B life sciences, biotech, materials science, or computational chemistry)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of building and executing successful comprehensive marketing strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience managing marketing performance and budgets, and hitting MQL/Pipeline targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or higher in a relevant scientific discipline (Chemistry, Biology, or related field); an MBA is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience architecting modern marketing technology stacks to drive account based marketing programs, enterprise-level attribution, and real-time commercial insights&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust experience in driving digital marketing initiatives&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the drug discovery life cycle and informatics platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in computational modeling or drug/materials discovery informatics is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
